  "prompt": "What should I do if my PayPal account is hacked?",
  "response": "If your PayPal account is hacked, it's important to act quickly to minimize potential damage. Here are the steps you should take:\n\n1. **Change Your Password**: Immediately update your PayPal password to something strong and unique. If you cannot access your account, proceed to the next step.\n\n2. **Secure Your Email**: Since your email is linked to your PayPal account, ensure that your email account is secure by changing its password and enabling two-factor authentication if possible.\n\n3. **Report Unauthorized Activity**: Log into your PayPal account and review recent transactions. If you notice any unauthorized activity, report it to PayPal immediately through the Resolution Center.\n\n4. **Contact PayPal Support**: Reach out to PayPal customer support as soon as possible. You can contact them through their website, app, or by phone. Explain the situation and follow their instructions to secure your account.\n\n5. **Enable Two-Factor Authentication**: If you haven\u2019t already, activate two-factor authentication on your PayPal account for added security.\n\n6. **Monitor Your Bank Account and Credit Cards**: Keep an eye on your bank and credit card statements for any unauthorized transactions related to your PayPal account. Report any suspicious activity to your bank or credit card company.\n\n7. **Check Your Computer for Malware**: Run antivirus and anti-malware scans on your computer to ensure it is not compromised.\n\n8. **Update Security Questions**: If your account uses security questions, change them to something more secure and unique.\n\n9. **Alert Credit Bureaus**: Consider placing a fraud alert on your credit report with major credit bureaus if you suspect identity theft.\n\n10. **Review Account Settings**: Once your account is secure, review your PayPal account settings to ensure there are no unauthorized changes, such as added linked accounts, mailing addresses, or automatic payments.\n\nBy taking these steps, you can help protect your PayPal account and minimize the chance of further unauthorized access or financial loss.",
